                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13007.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">R. Zubáran Capmany</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The Department of State respectfully acknowledges the receipt of the note of Mr.
                    E. Zubáran Capmany, dated the 25th instant, saying that on the twenty-second day
                    of August of this year, General Don Venustiano Carranza, Chief of the
                    Constitutionalist Army of Mexico, took charge of the Executive power of the
                    Mexican Republic.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
